# Frontend Coding Standards — Portfolio

> Read `TECH_CONVENTIONS.md` for the full reference.

## TypeScript

- **No `any`.** Use interfaces for props; `interface` for object shapes; `type` for unions.
- Prop interfaces: `ComponentNameProps` (or local `type` for small components).
- Enums: `PascalCase` members (`TextButtonVariant.Primary`).
- Data constants: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` (`PROFILE`, `EXPERIENCES`).
- File suffixes: `*.util.ts`, `*.const.ts`, `*.type.ts`.

## Imports and exports

- Order: external → internal → relative → assets.
- **Named exports** for components; default export only where established (`App.tsx`).
- Barrel imports from `components/shared` when possible.

## Naming

- **camelCase** — variables, functions (`handleClick`, `isExternal`).
- **PascalCase** — components, enums, interfaces.
- **UPPER_SNAKE_CASE** — module-level constants.

## Components

- Match the export/style pattern of the file you edit (`React.FC` vs function declaration).
- Single responsibility; extract repeated logic to hooks or utils.
- No `console.log` in committed code.

## Styling

- Tailwind + semantic tokens; avoid custom CSS unless necessary.
- No hardcoded magic strings for copy—use `portfolio.const.ts`.

## Performance

- `useCallback` / `useMemo` only when justified (child callbacks, expensive work).

## Quality checklist

- [ ] No `any`
- [ ] Copy in constants when reusable
- [ ] Shared components reused
- [ ] `npm run build` passes
- [ ] Prettier-friendly formatting (single quotes, trailing commas)
